snippet.textDisplay:
If you train in an MMA gym with any pro fighters, no one in THAT WORLD would give up due to shoulder strikes FROM THE BEGINNING OF THE FIGHT. People are speaking about broken nose and headkicks, but cowboy did not attempt to throw a single punch, or even tried to defend himself during the fight. And hey, did you notice the old lady who hugged and kissed Mcgregor after the match? That was Cowboy's grandma, thanking Conor for picking his grandson Donald for the payday. A slow starting cowboy wouldn't come out the way he did, confused, not knowing what do, like he forgot how to defend himself, or saw a ghost. The beating was real, cowboy really took the beating, but the whole outcome of the fight was determined from the beginning. Cowboy was paid to lose. And although I hate saying that, I believe that Mcgregor would've won a real fight vs Cowboy but as big as he is now, he cannot lose at this stage because there are still a lot more money to make for the UFC, ESPN, and etc. Also Dana confirmed it during the post-fight press conference that is was staged. No one asked him a question about the fight and he brought it up himself stating that it wasn't fake.


PS. Cowboy threw one kick, as a signal for Mcgregor to left headkick him (a cowboy's special), which leads to a vintage Conor's signature 1st round TKO. What a beautiful comeback story, huh?


And no I am not a hater. Conor Mcgregor is amazing, and I always win money when he fights (it's so easy to predict his fights) but Mcgregor is now more of a show, rather than real combat fighting now.
